# Phase 2b: React 18 ŌåÆ 19 ŌĆö Implementation Log

## Prerequisites

Phases 5 (Zustand replaces Redux) and 6 (@dnd-kit replaces react-sortable-hoc) completed,
removing the two blockers for React 19: `react-redux@7` and `findDOMNode` usage.

## Step 1: Upgrade react + react-dom

- `react` ^18.3.1 ŌåÆ ^19
- `react-dom` ^18.3.1 ŌåÆ ^19

Used `--force` due to transitive peer dep warnings (all compatible at runtime).

## Step 2: Upgrade @testing-library/react

- `@testing-library/react` ^14.3.1 ŌåÆ ^16 (v16.1.0+ supports React 19)
- Added `@testing-library/dom` ^10.4.1 as explicit devDependency (RTL v16 moved it to a peer dep)

## Step 3: Remove unused `import React from 'react'`

With the automatic JSX runtime (available since React 17, configured via `@vitejs/plugin-react`),
the default React import is unnecessary. Removed from 8 files:

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| `src/index.tsx` | `import React` ŌåÆ `import { StrictMode }` |
| `src/App.tsx` | Removed `import React` |
| `src/App.test.tsx` | Removed `import React` |
| `src/components/index.tsx` | `import React, { ReactNode }` ŌåÆ `import { ReactNode }` |
| `src/components/SortableList/SortableList.tsx` | `import React, { useEffect }` ŌåÆ `import { useEffect }` |
| `src/components/Header/Header.tsx` | Removed `import React` |
| `src/components/HamburgerMenu/Menu.tsx` | Removed `import React` |
| `src/components/Button/Button.tsx` | Removed `import React` |
| `src/components/InfoView/InfoView.tsx` | Removed `import React` |

Also updated `<React.StrictMode>` ŌåÆ `<StrictMode>` in index.tsx (using named import).

